description.2: Spider-Man faces off against the menacing Brotherhood of Scriers! Can Ben save Traveller and Chakra - while still making it out in one piece?
description.7: Both SPECTACULAR and a classic foe gets revamped, as Spidey battles an army of reptiles and the resurrected, savage and now-intelligent Lizard!
description.9: Navigators and explorers are a special breed - they blaze the paths others will follow. They must have strength, drive, and hope, and be more than a little fearless. But nowhere is it written that they must have luck. Gav and Jori Daragon make their living charting the routes of hyperspace and selling those routes to traders and haulers. When a starswarm cluster batters their ship, they land on the planet Cinnagar, destitute and forlorn, and convince the relatively amiable Aarrba the Hutt to make the necessary repairs.
description.10: Leia has been captured by Prince Xizor, underlord of the galaxy's most ruthless criminal organization, and Han Solo has been encased in carbonite by Darth Vader, a package Boba Fett intends to deliver to Jabba the Hutt. As the Rebels approach their most deperate hour, it appears as though their long battle may be at an end. But looks can be deceiving in the Shadows of the Empire!
description.14: With Ravencroft shutting down, John Jameson attempts to imprison Carnage in his own twisted mind, but when the tables are turned, it's the inmate who takes control of the asylum!
description.15: Kaine continues his campaign against Ben Reilly! And even though Ben is able to save his friend Janine, can he help her escape a murder accusation?
description.16: The Swarm is about to engulf New York City and it's up to Spider-Man to stop it! Plus - the gender of Peter and Mary Jane's baby is revealed!
description.21: Douglock is now a captive of Black Air! Meanwhile, the London Hellfire Club has a mole on the inside -- their new Black Bishop, Britanic!
description.22: The Hulk faces an old challenge with a new twist - the gamma radiation that powers him is leaking at a lethal rate! And with the military in hot pursuit, and his power draining, it seems his days are numbered. Is this at last the end of the Incredible Hulk?
description.23: The entire Marvel Universe pitted against Onslaught! From Hulk to the Avengers, from Fantastic Four to X-Men, the Marvel U leaves no stone unturned as they face their most dangerous adversary yet!
description.24: The crime bosses of NYC have gathered together to take advantage of the hero-less world, while turning their backs against Don Fortunato!
description.26: Role reversal! Professor X is in dire need of a pep talk and Wolverine is the one to give it to him. Meanwhile, Bastion plans mutantkind's downfall!
description.28: Guilty over the destruction of Onslaught, Professor X leaves his X-Men for a life of solitude. But with his team of mutants mentor-less, who will bring guidance in the darkest of times?
description.37: The Kingpin comes for Peter Parker… through Mary Jane! Peter may regret speaking his mind to Wilson Fisk after his girlfriend becomes Kingpin's hostage!
description.40: After the Onslaught epic, Spider-Man says farewell to fallen heroes.
description.41: Cable, infected with a techno-organic virus since birth, battles his toughest adversary yet; his growing sense of mortality!
description.44: Creators of the Onslaught Event take you inside the saga that forever changed Marvel's mutants. An insider's look at early concept art, as well as writer and artist interviews!
description.46: Throughout the vast reaches of'the galaxyM wherever fugitives meet or lawbreakers conspire, one name is always uttered in hushed tones, a name guaranteed to strike fear into the stoutest heart:'Boba Fett. His prices are exorbitant, but if you're looking for revenge, or if you're looking for protection, he'll get the job done. And if you're looking to reclaim your kidnapped fianc', the heiress to a'Hutt's fortune, no price is too exorbitant.
description.47: A handful of Tatooine outlaws and a mountain full of Imperial weaponry are a deadly combination-deadly enough to make allies of X-wing Rogue Squadron and a troop of Imperial Special Forces! The hot desert sands really heat up in the explosive conclusion to Battleground: Tatooine, as Wedge and crew attempt to take back the galaxy, one planet at a time!
description.49: A creepy, moody tale focusing on the tortured psyche of Curt Connors! What will the Doc do to change the planet he feels is falling apart? What is this new Lizard, really, and what will he do when he finds his former alter ego?
description.51: The bounty on Skywalker's head is good cold or warm, dead or alive. A live bounty will always bring a bigger reward than a dead one, but when the target leaves you no choice you take what you can get.
description.54: Alistaire reunites with Excalibur teammates back at the X-Mansion. In London, Shinobi Shaw of the Hellfire Club makes an offer to Brian Braddock...
description.55: Incredible Hulk vs. Onslaught! In this Incredible Hulk tie-in issue, the Hulk must team-up with the X-Men to take down their greatest telepathic foe. But will Hulk, in all his brawny might, still fall victim to the mind control of Onslaught? Plus, the fate of Rick Jones and Marlo Chandler revealed!
description.56: ONSLAUGHT IMPACT PART 2 Iron Man, Quicksilver, Giant-Man, and Black Panther take on a contingent of Sentinels.
description.57: The aftermath issue of Onslaught’s attack on Manhattan. Will Spider-Man be able to pick up the pieces in the wake of the storm? And who will take responsibility for the lives lost? A can’t-miss issue in the Onslaught event!
description.58: Thor and Red Norvell flee New York after they are driven away by Onslaught. Before the end of existence, Thor reminisces about his past in Asgard.
description.59: Fantastic Four tie-in issue with the Onslaught event! Will the FF be able to aid the X-Men as they take on the greatest psychic mastermind? And how do you defeat an enemy without a tangible body?
description.60: The X-Men, the Avengers, and the Fantastic Four endeavor to free Xavier from the psionic clutches of Onslaught!
description.61: Reeling from the Onslaught attack, Logan retreats from the main battlefield to aid those who are unable to defend themselves. But wherever Wolverine goes, a ghost from his past isn't far behind. Enter Elektra's old guru, Stick, who has returned to give Wolverine a lesson in humanity.
description.62: Joseph, a de-aged version of Magneto, and Rogue, join forces to go full throttle on Onslaught's Sentinel army. Magneto and Rogue- no holds barred!
description.66: Ben is finally settling into life as Spider-Man, but suddenly one of his most notorious enemies returns again to strike! KAINE LIVES!
description.67: The Avengers attempt to take Spider-Man into custody when genetically-altered bodies are found strung up in spider webs across New York City! In Mexico, a couple makes a horrifying discovery.
description.70: Punisher feels the impact of Onslaught after the Helicarrier falls. How many lives will be lost in this destruction? And will Punisher be able to re-gain control after chaos reigns supreme? It's Onslaught versus the Island of Manhattan!
description.71: Phil Urich is the new Green Goblin. After Onslaught unleashes a fleet of Sentinels on the city, will Goblin make a personal sacrifice to save innocent lives? An exciting twist in the Green Goblin saga with this Onslaught crossover issue!
description.74: Onslaught tie-in! Nate Grey confronts his most feared villain, Mister Sinister. Featuring the Marauders and Franklin Richards!
description.79: Onslaught uses a fleet of Sentinels to seize the city. After a Sentinel attack on the Daily Bugle, J. Jonah Jameson is actually happy see Spider-Man save the day. A Spider-Man/Onslaught crossover issue!
description.80: In the aftermath of Onslaught, the Avengers must commit to damage control. While trying to contain the wide spread damage, the team is attacked by the two mutants Post and Holocaust.
description.81: Part of the Onslaught crossover. Cable confronts the enemy that has sought his death since birth. Cable vs. Apocalypse!
description.83: In an unlikely alliance, the X-Men join Magneto and his Brotherhood to take out the true foe behind the Russian/U.S. Missile Crisis… Apocalypse!
description.86: Jabba the Hutt is dead, and in the ensuing scramble for power, a secret Imperial weapons cache could be the key to victory. But only one being alive knows the location of the hidden weapons cache -- Firith Olan. While that makes Firith a very powerful being, it also makes him a prime target. In a desperate race to uncover the missing weapons, as the criminals converge to fill the role of the dead Hutt, Wedge and Rogue Squadron find themselves smack in the middle of Battleground: Tatooine!
description.88: Apocalypse awakens and consults the Watcher. And Onslaught gathers his minions!
description.89: Can Peter survive this mysterious illness which has befallen him?
description.90: What would it take for you to step into the den of a rancor? What treasure would tempt you to stare death in the face? Aboard Boba Fett's ship is a carbonite-encased Han Solo. Jabba's willing to pay plenty for Solo, making him a tempting treasure for every bounty hunter in the galaxy. But tempting enough to board the Slave I? Apparently, somebody thinks so!
description.92: All hope seems lost for Peter Parker, who is sick and dying. Can Ben save the beloved former Spider-Man from his obvious fate? Maybe, but with some unlikely help.
description.95: Nightcrawler must confront past demons in his battle with Red Queen. Meanwhile, London burns and Jean Grey and Cyclops finally arrive at Muir Island. But will their arrival prove too late?
description.96: Storm gets involved in the fray between Cable and Hulk. Will the Weather Goddess' elemental powers prove puny in the presence of the almighty Hulk? An epic smack-down you have to see to believe!
description.97: Iron Man faces off against Unicorn while Morgan Stark's machinations continue behind the scenes.
description.98: While Peter Parker is on his deathbed, things take an even worse turn when Hammerhead checks into the same hospital! It's up to Ben Reilly to ensure this latest threat to Peter stays at bay!
description.99: The Atlantean warriors will not stop their attack on Alchemax and things only get worse for Spider-Man when the Vulture joins the fight!

0.text: Howard the Duck starts (and ends) a bar brawl in Los Angeles! Tores enters the scene, and Beast makes a critical discovery about M.

3.text: The Psycho-Man is to blame for a rise in anti-mutant sentiment! After a strange encounter in an abandoned movie theater, Copycat is kidnapped while wearing Kane’s face!

4.text: The FINAL issue of the mysterious thriller is here! Read the finale to this limited series, and see if Kitty & Pete have the strength within them to defeat their murderous foe.

5.text: Venom gets revenge after Dr. Paine steals Eddie’s symbiote and subjects it to torture.

6.text: Steven Hudak sets things aflame as the Scorcher!

7.text: Both SPECTACULAR and a classic foe gets revamped, as Spidey battles an army of reptiles and the resurrected, savage and now-intelligent Lizard!

11.text: Iron Fist faces his greatest challenge at the hands of the merciless Steel Serpent! Can Danny Rand rise to the challenge, or will he, and the hidden city of K'un-Lun fall?

12.text: This special tribute pays homage to the history and origin of Marvel's First Family! Delve into the past, as many of Marvel's mightiest creators explore the Fantastic Four's history as adventurers!

13.text:
Before he was Apocalypse...he was En Sabah Nur. The origins of one of the X-Men's greatest foes are at last revealed - from his upbringing thousands of years ago! Can Pharaoh Rama-Tut get to the future Apocalypse and his adopted father Baal before Apocalypse's evil destiny can manifest itself?
Age Rating: 12+  High Definition

14.text: With Ravencroft shutting down, John Jameson attempts to imprison Carnage in his own twisted mind, but when the tables are turned, it's the inmate who takes control of the asylum!

15.text: Kaine continues his campaign against Ben Reilly! And even though Ben is able to save his friend Janine, can he help her escape a murder accusation?

17.text: When X-Force corners Shatterstar for answers, they uncover even more questions. Cable is straddling the line between his own instincts and those of the team…is Shatterstar too far gone to be trusted?

18.text: The Abomination proves an ugly, menacing foe for X-Man. But with Threnody's life hanging in the balance, Nate must pull out all the stops!

20.text: The Enforcers capture Daredevil! But he needs to escape so he can defend Mr. Hyde in court!

24.text: The crime bosses of NYC have gathered together to take advantage of the hero-less world, while turning their backs against Don Fortunato!

27.text: Wolverine and Elektra travel to Greece, where they come closer to Logan's mysterious past than they both realize!

30.text: Hercules returns to the Avengers’ home base to a horrifying discovery. Where have all the Avengers gone?!

31.text: Someone's stolen Japan's most powerful weapon: the mighty Red Ronin! Now Wolverine, Yukio and Sunfire must unite to prevent the total destruction of the Far East!

32.text: A series of dimensional rifts have been opened and several of the X-Men have fallen into them.

33.text: If the X-Men want to save Hannah Connover from an alien infection, they must defeat the Queen Brood! But Jean Grey has reservations about this strategy, and the X-Men decide to find another way to infiltrate the Brood.

34.text: Death, Danger, and Mystery! Learn more about how our mysterious killer is turning people into mummies, and if there is anything Kitty and Pete can do to stop it. Can they find him before it is too late?

35.text: His Goblin glider is destroyed and his Bugle career may be coming to an end…Which direction will Phil take when he can no longer play the hero?

36.text: Newly freed from Dr. Paine’s laboratory, Eddie must now hunt his ravenously mad symbiote!

38.text: Jubilee faces a rite of passage courtesy of the savage Sabretooth!

39.text: Avenging speedster Quicksilver flits into the Uncanny Origins spotlight! Revisit some of Pietro Maximoff’s first days with the Brotherhood of Mutants, and explore his unique relationship with twin sister Scarlet Witch!

42.text: Chamber and Skin get a lift from Howard the Duck! Emma Frost experiences a nightmarish psychic vision.

45.text: There are more than fifty billion droids at work throughout the galaxy, doing the jobs better handled by hard metal than by soft flesh. Human muscles strain and grow weak, and Human hearts grow weary of toil and indignity; droids have no such problems. They have no bones, and they have no souls. And when Humans grow old and feeble, they must be cared for, must be clothed and fed, that is their right. But droids have no rights, and so they end up here, in the vast, corroded canyons of Ronyards.

48.text: Who is the Black Knight? Spider-Man suffers a devastating loss when Bluebird loses her wings.

49.text: A creepy, moody tale focusing on the tortured psyche of Curt Connors! What will the Doc do to change the planet he feels is falling apart? What is this new Lizard, really, and what will he do when he finds his former alter ego?

50.text: Spider-Man struggles between taking time to recover in the hospital, versus resuming hero duties. Against Aunt May’s insistence, Spidey takes to the costume again, but soon wishes he had stayed in bed! It’s Spider-Man vs. the Looter!

52.text: X-Factor avoids the Dark Beast's deceptions and rescues the real Beast. Havok and Random square off against Polaris, but the winner soon hits Polaris below the belt.

53.text: Daredevil and Misty Knight team up to do some investigating on Mr. Hyde’s case!

57.text: The aftermath issue of Onslaught’s attack on Manhattan. Will Spider-Man be able to pick up the pieces in the wake of the storm? And who will take responsibility for the lives lost? A can’t-miss issue in the Onslaught event!

64.text: A new saga for the Iron Fist begins here! Daniel Rand is blessed with the mystic power of K’un-Lun’s most ancient force. But when the Steel Serpent, Iron Fist’s most antagonistic foe, steals the power of the Dragon for himself, who will suffer? Danny Rand, Iron Fist no longer?

65.text: Cyclops and Phoenix at last return to the present…or try to, that is! Standing in their way is the newly transformed Mr. Sinister, destined to become one of their greatest foes…if they can survive!

66.text: Ben is finally settling into life as Spider-Man, but suddenly one of his most notorious enemies returns again to strike! KAINE LIVES!

67.text: The Avengers attempt to take Spider-Man into custody when genetically-altered bodies are found strung up in spider webs across New York City! In Mexico, a couple makes a horrifying discovery.

68.text: Young Hannah Connover is implanted with an egg from the Brood, an alien race that has ravaged humanity for years. After Jean Grey shares a nightmare with Hannah, the X-Men must save the Connover family from the strange effects of Hannah’s implantation. Have the X-Men underestimated the power of the Brood?

69.text: The “Onslaught” continues! How will Gen X fare in the Garden of Unearthly Delights?

72.text: Onslaught plays mind games with X-Force! The team is scattered in telepathic planes, or trapped in the rubble of Xavier’s mansion. What is reality and what is artificial reality becomes confused, as each member re-lives the darkest time of their life, or sees their greatest fear realized.

73.text: Cain Marko thought he was in control of the Cyttorak…until the gem claims him for itself! Juggernaut is filled with all the rage -- but has nowhere to channel it!

76.text: In this one-time release by Marvel, follow our main characters, Kitty Pryde & Pete Wisdom, as they try to save the world from a mutant serial killer. If you are interested in investigative thrillers with plenty of mystery, this is the series for you!

77.text: A special event detailing the life and times of Odin's favorite son. Over ten tales from Asgard brought to you by powerhouse talent!

78.text: Eddie Brock and his symbiote are separated, and when Brock gets institutionalized, Dr. Paine becomes his primary care giver. The symbiote must find a new host that will curb his appetite for brains!

82.text: Spider-Man faces off with the Puppet Master as a gallery show goes awry!

84.text: Read the origin of founding X-Man Cyclops! From optic-blasting orphan, to leader of the X-Men, see some of Scott Summers’ earliest adventures before he met Charles Xavier!

85.text: A stormtrooper remembers a young woman on the planet Lurr, and he remembers how she died at his hands. The wind rises to drown his screams. The shadows rise to drown his soul. Whether your sins are great or whether they are trivial, when the eyes of Clat the Shamer are upon you, your guilt will be the same- unbearable.

87.text: With Bluebird’s assist, Spidey manages to take out Vulture…and the Scarlet Beetle!

88.text: Apocalypse awakens and consults the Watcher. And Onslaught gathers his minions!

89.text: Can Peter survive this mysterious illness which has befallen him?

91.text: Dismay between Dr. Essex and his wife leads him to form a dark alliance with Apocalypse…allowing the despotic mutant to transform him forever! MR. SINISTER IS BORN!

92.text: All hope seems lost for Peter Parker, who is sick and dying. Can Ben save the beloved former Spider-Man from his obvious fate? Maybe, but with some unlikely help.

93.text: Spider-Man joins forces with Power Man and Iron Fist to take on the badder-than-ever Scorpion!

94.text: After a fight with Pyro, Matt Murdock agrees to take on Mr. Hyde as a client when a viable case pops up!

98.text: While Peter Parker is on his deathbed, things take an even worse turn when Hammerhead checks into the same hospital! It's up to Ben Reilly to ensure this latest threat to Peter stays at bay!
